1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nxe5
{ By far the most common move, entering the big mainline of the Petroff. } 3...
Nxe4 4. Nxf7
{ Starting from this variation, we will take a look at White's rare tries on the 4th move. 4.Nxf7 is a dubious but interesting gambit in the @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.e4  e5  2.Nf3  Nf6  3.Nxe5  d6  4.Nxf7  variation. However, here, it loses on the spot. }
4... Qe7
{ Unstereotypical idea, but it just wins.  4...Kxf7??  5.Qh5+  would let White get the Knight back with one of the checks. }
5. Nxh8 Nc3+
{ The point. We use the same exact trick White wanted to use against us by playing 4. Qe2. Ha! }
