10. Qe2 { White usually tries to create some complications with Qh5 next. }
10... f4 11. Qh5+ { This is how White usually tries to get some compensation. }
11... Qf7 { The simplest. } 12. Qxg5 fxg3 13. hxg3 Qf5
{ We will either exchange Queens or take on e5 or c2 next. White has three pawns for the piece, but he has multiple weaknesses, and in such an open position, pieces are much more valuable. Game over! }
