{ Simple. We are ready to continue with ... Ng6/Nc6 if nothing concrete is going on. There is also ... Bxb5 and only then ... Nc6. Engines already give us full equality. }
11. Be3 Bxb5 { Simple. } 12. Nxb5 a6
{ Any problems with the queenside are only illusionary. We can play either ... Nc6/Ng6 or even ... Qb4 or ... g6 next. Black is by no means worse. There is only one line I want to show you. }
13. Qf5+ Rd7
{ Since we played ... Rd7 in the previous line, I suggest sticking to it here as well. If White doesn't want to be worse he should try  14.Bf4  axb5  15.Bxe5  and now  15...g6  16.Qf4  Bh6  is more than fine for Black.   The reason why I extended the line is that  13...Kb8?!  allows  14.Rfd1!  when the threat of Qxe5 makes our setup awkward. }
