{ In this chapter, we will take a look at White's rare tries on move five and four.    With 5. d3, instead of taking the hanging Knight, White spends a tempo to force it to a better and more stable square. Thanks, I guess... }
5... Nf6
{ Next is ... d6 or ... Nc6 with full equality. If you decide on ... Nc6 and White takes, always recapture with the d-pawn. }
