[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nxe5 Nxe4 4. Qe2 Qe7 5. Nf3
{ This really makes no sense. } 5... d5
{ Simple. White has to finish development in some way, and there are only two decent options here. If White doesn't hit the e4-Knight, we can simply develop with ... Bf5/Bg4, ... Nc6 and castle queenside. }
6. Nc3
{ I decided to add this variation because most players take on c3 here which is a mistake. }
6... c6
{ We should take on c3 only if White is forced to recapture with the b-pawn. It is the same thing I talked about in the comment to the very first line of the current chapter - always retake with the d-pawn to avoid the weakening of the pawn structure and isolating the a-pawn.   6...Nxc3?!  7.dxc3  gives White good chances for an edge.   After  6...c6  , if White plays slowly, we can keep developing. If White hits the Knight with  7.d3  , we should go for  7...Nxc3  since taking with the d-pawn is no longer an option. }
