{ We challenge the Knight and either plan to take on e5 next. We have a better pawn structure temporarily, and I can imagine scenarios when we play ... c6 and ... b5 in the middlegame, fixing White's pawns on the c-file.   White's best chance is something like  8.Bf4  Nxe5  9.Qxe5  Qxe5  10.Bxe5  , and here, we don't have to lose time on defending the c-pawn, but  10...Bf5  is fine. First, we hit the c2-pawn, and second, we always can meet Bxc7 with ... Rc8. }
