{ This way of attacking our Knight is incorrect. We can transpose to the first chapters of the course by playing  4...Qe7  5.Qxe4  d6  etc. but there is something much stronger. }
4... Ng5
{ We win a tempo and plan to simply castle kingside next. In case of any issues, the Knight will be relocated to e6. }
5. Qe3 Be7
{ ... O-O and ... d6 are next and then ... Re8 followed by ... d5 at some point with some edge for us. Another plan worth considering is to play ... d5 in one go and only then ... c5. }
