4... d5
{ We should do exactly the same. The d-pawn will land on d5 sooner or later and it is questionable if the Knight's presence on e5 is bad or not. Therefore, we ignore it and grab a fair share of space. It also fits our strategy of playing symmetrically, only to break the symmetry to our benefit later. }
