{ I think that sacrificing the b7-pawn is the best way forward. It also fits our strategy of preparing ... b6 and ... c5. }
13. Qc3 { This is more dangerous. White stops ... b6 due to Qc6. } 13... Rb8
{ We renew the idea of ... b6 followed by ... c5. It works here because we will be able to meet Qc6 with ... Qd7 and there is no hanging Rook on a8. }
14. Rxb7 { There is nothing else. } 14... Rxb7 15. Qc6+ Qd7 16. Qxb7 c5
{ White is not in time to prevent us from castling and stop the exchange of Queens at the same time. }
17. Qxa6 { 17.Qa8+  Qc8  doesn't change much. } 17... O-O 18. Bxc5 Rc8
{ We will go for ... Bf5 when we will deprive White of the Bishop pair advantage. Only Black can be better here. }
