{ White has all kinds of plans here - Nc3, Nd2, Re1, c4 or even Qh5. All of them have a different flavour, so let's quickly take a look at them! }
8. Re1
{ This is quite risky. Maybe not because of  8...Bxh2+  9.Kxh2  Qh4+  which results only in a draw with perfect play, but due to the following idea. }
8... O-O
{ A powerful pawn sacrifice. Now, when  9.Nd2  runs into  9...Bxh2+  and  9.Nc3  into  9...Nxf2  in both cases with a crushing attack, White really has to take. }
9. Bxe4 dxe4 10. Rxe4 Bc6
{ This looks like the best Marshall Gambit possible. The Rook has to go back to the 1st or 2nd rank when we will continue with ... Qh4 with an ongoing attack. }
11. d5 Bxd5
{ I just wanted to point out this small trick! The Bishop is taboo due to ... Bxh2+. }
