{ The most common plan, keeping all the options open and developing the Rook where it belongs anyway. }
11... c6
{ We should play flexibly as well. Now is the time when White has to commit to something, especially since we have the idea of ... b5 hanging in the air. We don't really want to rush with it, but when we play ... b5, White won't be able to play c4 ever, and both c-pawns will be fixed. }
12. Bg5
{ Almost exclusively played. It also makes the most sense, so we look only at this idea. Note that in this specific order,  12.Rb1  is wrong due to  12...b5!  instead of ... b6. }
12... Qc7
{ White has two promising plans at his disposal - either strike with the c-pawn or transfer the Rook to the kingside/double the Rooks on the e-file. }
13. c4 Be8 { Standard. } 14. Qh3
{ The most natural square, hitting f5 from two directions. } 14... dxc4 15.
Bxc4+
{ 15.Bxf5  h6!  should met with the same exact sequence as inthis variation. }
15... Bf7 16. Be6
{ 16.Bd3  g6  is also fine. Weakening the kingside with ... g6 would be maybe a bit problematic with the White Queen on h4, but when our rival has the Queen on h3, it will take some extra time to create anything on the dark squares. In general, ... Rfe8 is next. }
16... Bxe6
{ But not  16...g6?!  17.Qb3!  which is extremely unpleasant to deal with. }
17. Rxe6 Rae8
{ I wanted to end the line here, but since the following few moves are pretty forced for both sides, I decided to show you the whole thing. }
18. Rae1 { 18.Rxe8  Rxe8  19.Qxf5  doesn't win a pawn due to  19...Bxh2+  . }
18... Rxe6 19. Rxe6 Qb6
{ A very strong move. We don't go for some passive approach, but play the most active move instead. White has to watch out for the weak 1st rank as well as the hanging pawn on d4. }
20. Qb3
{ The best defence. White consolidates and prepares a discovered attack on our King. }
20... Qxb3
{ It might look sub-optimal to improve White's pawns like this, but after the exchange of Queens, our position will be straightforward to handle. }
21. axb3 Bb4
{ ... h6 followed by ... Kf7 is coming. We also have the potential to create a passed pawn on the queenside. We equalized fully. Enough of this mainline Petroff thing - let's check the sidelines! }
