1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Bd3
{ If someone plays like this against you, your biggest challenge is not to die from laughter. }
3... d5 { White can't even take on d5 due to ... e4. } 4. Nc3 dxe4
{ In the vast majority of games, White will blunder here. } 5. Nxe4
{ 5.Bxe4  is better but after  5...Nxe4  6.Nxe4  Nc6  with ... f5 to come, Black has more space and the Bishop pair, resulting in a big advantage for us. }
