1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Bd3
{ If someone plays like this against you, your biggest challenge is not to die from laughter. }
3... d5 { White can't even take on d5 due to ... e4. } 4. Qe2
{ This is White's 2nd most common try. } 4... Bd6
{ We couldn't care less about losing the central pawn. White has the King on e1 and the Queen on e2, so we would love to have the e-file opened. }
5. exd5 Nxd5
{ We are ready not only to castle, but to play ... Nf4/Nb4 as well. } 6. Nxe5
O-O
