8. f5 Qg7 { The point. } 9. fxg6 hxg6 10. Qg4
{ This is a more direct way of attacking our position. Since both Qxg6 and Nxg6 are threats and the kingside is weakened, we will use a surprising resource. }
10... Kd8
{ Not only do we step out of danger, but by defending the Bishop, we create the threat of ... d5.   10...g5?  11.Nf5  with Bd3 to come is wrong.  With  10... Kd8, we dodge both captures.   •  11.Qxg6  drops the Knight.   •  11.Nxg6  d5  allows a discovered attack on the Queen. }
