9. Bxd5 { Now, let me demonstrate the whole point of our plan. } 9... c6
{ No matter where the Bishop goes, we will throw in ... Bc5+ followed by the exchange of Queens and then ... e4. }
10. Bc4 Bc5+
{ Just remember to give this check first to force the King to h1. } 11. Kh1
Qxd1 12. Rxd1 e4
{ We will eventually support the pawn with ... f5. We can also play ... a5 to make sure the Bishop won't be hit with b4. In general, we should be delighted with the pawn structure we have now. All pawn endgames are completely winning and White's 4v3 on the queenside is meaningless. }
