5. Ba4
{ It looks perfectly natural to move the Bishop to a4, but it is extremely risky. Amazingly, it is the most common choice for White over the board! }
5... c6
{ We prepare both ... a5, ... b5 chasing the Bishop, while ... d5 is also an idea. }
6. O-O { The safest choice, but we can launch the queenside now. } 6... a5
{ We threaten ... b5 followed by ... a4. } 7. a3
{ 7.Bb3  allows the simple  7...d6  threatening ... Bg4, when we have an edge in this relatively symmetrical position. Out initiative on the queenside should tell in the future. }
7... Bc5
{ We speed up kingside castling. Next, we want to play ... b5, ... d6 and ... O-O. }
8. Nxe5 { Only this move forces us to change plans. } 8... d6 9. Nd3
