3. Nc3
{ I don't think this is the correct approach. First, we can transpose to the 3.f4 Vienna after  3...Nf6  , but there is something even more appealing and practical. }
3... dxe4
{ Even though  3...exf4  is theoretically correct, I would bet my money on getting a safe and stable advantage. }
4. Nxe4 { 4.fxe5  Bf5  is also excellent for Black. } 4... Nf6
{ There is no point in entering any nonsense. We will take on e4 if White defends the Knight with a pawn or a minor piece, while if White defends the Knight with the Queen, then we will play ... Nc6 threatening ... Nd4. I just want to point out the most common sequence in faster time controls. }
5. Nxf6+ { Played 649 times out of 1047 games. } 5... Qxf6 6. fxe5
{ And 372 times out of 653 games. } 6... Qh4+ { We win on the spot. } *

