{ We can assume that taking on d5 is not a good option due to ... Nxd5 and we have a perfect version of the Isolated Queen Pawn positions. }
5. e5 c5
{ What we have on the board in some sort of an Advanced French structure without the pawns on e6 and c3, which certainly helps Black because the c8-Bishop can breathe. }
6. dxc5 { Otherwise, White's centre will fall. } 6... Nec6
{ The correct Knight. We make sure one of White's pawns will fall @@StartBracket@@or both@@EndBracket@@. ... d4 or ... Nd7 can be next while we can take the pawn on c5 whenever we want. }
