7. Bxf7+ { This is the only way to muddy the waters. } 7... Kxf7 8. Qb3+
{ The other check  8.Qd5+?!  Kf8  9.Qxe4  Bxc3+  10.bxc3  Qe7  enables the exchange of Queens and we end up with an extra pawn. }
8... d5 { The only move. } 9. Qxb4 Nc6
{ Next is ... Nxc3 followed by ... Re8+ and ... Kg8. Again, I don't see compensation for White. }
