6. e5
{ This is the only challenging move. Note that against all slow approaches such as Bd3, we should remember that the first moment when the c3-Knight is allowed to move @@StartBracket@@after castling kingside most of the time@@EndBracket@@, we should just take it to stop any Nd5 nonsense. }
6... Ne4
{ Since we don't have ... d5 and ... Ng4 is wrong because we don't have the Knight on c6 to pressurize e5, putting the Knight on e4 is the obvious option. }
7. Qd4 { Anything else either enables us to take on c3 or play ... d5. } 7...
Bxc3+ 8. bxc3 d5 9. exd6
{ This would have been an amazing move if not for our response. } 9... O-O
{ ... Nxd6 or ... Nc6 is next. The Knight is taboo of course.   I also want to point out that  10.dxc7  Qxc7!  doesn't drop material after  11.Qxe4??  due to  11...Qxc3+  . }
*

