7. Qd4 { Anything else either enables us to take on c3 or play ... d5. } 7...
Bxc3+ 8. bxc3 d5 9. Bb5+
{ The best move, trying to create some havoc on our queenside. } 9... c6
{ The simplest. } 10. Bd3 c5
{ An important move, grabbing space and preparing to part with the extra pawn for positional dividends. }
