{ I also pondered  11...Nc6  12.O-O  Be6  , but White has ideas such as  13.c4  or  13.Re1  followed by c4. The text is simpler. }
12. O-O
{ 12.Bxe4  dxe4  13.Qxe4  leads to a simple edge for us due to the better pawn structure. You can choose between  13...h6  , to increase control over the dark squares or  13...Qd7  to invade the light squares. }
12... f5 { We make sure the e5-pawn will evaporate. } 13. exf6 Qxf6 14. Bxe4
dxe4
{ Now after  15.Qxe4  we can play  15...Qf5  .   After  15.Ng5  both  15...Qe5  and  15...Qc6  are definitely OK. We have a structural advantage in both cases and can confidently look into the future. }
