10. Bg5 Bd7 { A critical move. } 11. Nd5
{ Note that  11.Bxf6?  Qxf6!  12.Rxd7  Bxc3  is winning for Black. } 11... e3
{ A key move, breaking communication between White's pieces. Not only is ... exf2 a threat but so is ... Bd2+. }
12. Qh4
{ White's army on the kingside looks impressive, but we have adequate resources to counter White's attacking plans. }
12... Bd2+ { This check has to be included before doing anything else. } 13.
Kb1 Bf5
{ Let's make sure we won't get mated! The Bishop is ready to block the g-file - just in case. }
14. Nxf6+ gxf6 15. Bxf6 Qd6
{ The only move to save the Queen and prepare to meet Qh6 at the same time. }
16. Qh6 Qf8 { We didn't win any material, but our position is dominant. } *

