[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nxe5 Nxe4 4. Qe2 Qe7 5. Qxe4 d6 6. d4 dxe5 7. dxe5 Nc6
8. f4 Bg4 9. Bd3 Qh4+ 10. g3 Qh3 11. Nc3 O-O-O 12. Be3 f5 13. exf6 Ba3
{ This is the moment where one of the variations has ended. Black has a very promising position with both ... Rhe8 and ... Bxb2 being threatened. }
14. bxa3
{ Capturing the Bishop is the most obvious idea, but it involves agreeing on the Queen's sacrifice. }
14... Rhe8 { The Queen can't move anywhere because ... Rxe3 would be deadly. }
15. fxg7 { Only this way. } 15... Rxe4
{ After both moves, Black should play ... Qh6 and collect the annoying pawn. }
16. Nxe4 Qg2
{ Yilmaz decides to go for the attack. However, White can hold with precise defence. Objectively better was  16...Qh6  , when the g7-pawn has to fall. Black should have a slight edge although the position is for three results for sure. }
17. Nf2 { Defending the Rook and threatening Be4. } 17... Qf3
{ With both ... Qxe3 and ... Re8 being threatened, White has only one acceptable option. }
18. Bc5
{ Both  18.Kd2??  Qe2+  and  18.Bd2??  Re8+  19.Kf1  Bh3+  are lost for White. }
18... Qd5 19. Bf8
{ This was the main reason behind the move Bc5. White blocks the 8th rank and keeps the options of promoting the pawn. Note that in this position, Nxg4 is a threat because after ... Qxh1+ Kf2 Qxa1, White can simply promote the pawn. }
19... Re8+ 20. Kf1 { 20.Kd2??  Re2+  loses on the spot. } 20... Nd4
{ A strong move, covering the f3-square and threatening  21.--  22...Bh3+  23.Nxh3  Qxh1+  24.Kf2  Qf3+  25.Kg1  Ne2+  with a mate in three to come. }
21. Re1
{ The only move. White has to cover e2 and challenge our Rook at the same time. }
21... Bh3+
{ Now, one of the most amazing variations I have ever seen will be played. }
22. Nxh3 Qxh1+ 23. Ng1 Rxe1+ 24. Kxe1 Qxg1+ 25. Kd2
{ Having this position over the board, I would be absolutely sure I am winning. Well, the position is equal! }
25... Nf3+ 26. Ke2 Nd4+ 27. Kd2 Nf3+ 28. Ke2 Nd4+ 29. Kd2 Nf3+ 30. Ke2
{ It seems White wasn't interested in allowing  30.Kc3  Qd4# } *

