[Black "Yiyi1984 vs. Kaldas90 / Rated Blitz lichess.org / 04.11.2021"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nc3 Nc6 4. d4 exd4 5. Nxd4 Nxe4 6. Nxc6 Nxc3 7. Nxd8
Nxd1 8. Nxf7 Kxf7 9. Kxd1 d5
{ I followed this line from the theoretical section. The position might look innocent, but after one or two inaccuracies from White, it can become highly problematic for our opponent. }
10. Bd3 Bg4+ { I decided that provoking f3 should only benefit me. } 11. f3 Be6
12. Be3 Bd6
{ The position is relatively equal, but after the incoming ... c5, it is obvious that Black has the initiative. }
13. c3 c5 14. Kd2 { I think it was safer to move the King towards f2. } 14...
Rac8 { This move turns out to be a waste of time.  14...b5!  was powerful. }
15. Rae1 b5
{ Black has all kinds of ideas connected with ... b4 or ... d4 followed by ... c4. }
16. Bf2 d4
{ If White takes on e4, I planned ... c4 followed by ... Bb4+, winning the exchange. }
17. Bg3 Rhd8 18. Bxd6 Rxd6
{ It looks like White eased his defence by exchanging the Bishops, but it is exactly the opposite. I am left with three active pieces, and White's King is shaky.   As a result, the threat of ... dxc3+ followed by ... b4+ and ... c4 while ... Bxa2 can also be considered leads to a blunder. }
19. Bxb5 Rb8
{ White resigned. If the Bishop moves, b2 falls. The best way forward is to sac the exchange on e6, but it is only a temporary solution. }
*

